The issue is that the reactive is being run when it is created (i.e. when the event handler is associated). The values are correctly set (by the browser) to whatever you&#39;re passing in the URL (notice the bookmark generates the correct URL), but then they&#39;re being changed when the handler is executed on creation.

The solution is to pass `ignoreInit=TRUE` to `observeEvent` to have it not run the handler upon creation (thereby keeping your URL-passed values).

```R
# ...

server &lt;- function(input, output, session){

	# Reactive function to get the mpg based on car name
	car_mpg &lt;- reactive({
		req(input$Select_Car)
		return(mtcars[row.names(mtcars) %in% input$Select_Car, &quot;mpg&quot;])
	})

	# Update the MPG input
	observeEvent(input$Select_Car, {
		updateNumericInput(session, &quot;MPG&quot;, value = car_mpg())
	}, ignoreInit=TRUE) # notice the parameter has been passed here.
}

# ...
```

